featured_reviews.review_translated_text:
Dharashiv caves are believed to be constructed around the 5th-7th century. The first caves were discovered in the 10th century during the Rashtrakutas era,[5] while there has been debate over whether the caves are Buddhist or Jain creations.[2] It is believed that these caves were Buddhist in origin, but Later these were converted into monuments of Jainism.
This view is very nice, one must visit it.

featured_reviews.review_id:
Dharashiv caves are a series of old rock cut caves built around fifth century AD. Researchers say that they were originally Buddhist caves and were later patronized by Jains.

A couple of caves are serving as Jain temples and they are somewhat maintained. Other caves are in very bad condition and requires upkeep. No guards are posted for security and no guides are available.

The landscape and terrain are awesome. Need a couple hours to visit including transit time from Osmanabad. Single females better avoid. Open round the clock. No gate, no guards or time keepers. Free for all.
